Package com.intellij.psi.codeStyle.arrangement

Class MemberOrderService

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.intellij.psi.codeStyle.arrangement.MemberOrderService

  • public class MemberOrderService
extends java.lang.Object
    The whole arrangement idea is to allow to change file entries order according to the user-provided rules.

    That means that we can re-use the same mechanism during, say, new members generation - arrangement rules can be used to determine position where a new element should be inserted.

    This service provides utility methods for that.

    • Method Detail

      • getAnchor

        public PsiElement getAnchor(PsiElement member,
                            CommonCodeStyleSettings settings,
                            PsiElement context)
        Tries to find an element at the given context which should be the previous sibling for the given 'member'element according to the user-defined arrangement rules.

        E.g. the IDE might generate given 'member' element and wants to know element after which it should be inserted

        Parameters:
        member - target member which anchor should be calculated
        settings - code style settings to use
        context - given member's context
        Returns:
        given member's anchor if the one can be computed; given 'context' element if given member should be the first child null otherwise
